<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="198" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,757,1070]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,453,757,782]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">Diagnosis and comments.</emphasis>
As we did not study any specimens that fit the description of 
<emphasis box="[1145,1263,757,781]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">P. k roe b e r i</emphasis>
and the 
<typeStatus box="[1362,1410,758,782]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">type</typeStatus>
is destroyed, the following diagnosis is based on the original description (with terminology updated based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Cumming" box="[151,466,829,854]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" refString="Cumming, J. M. &amp; Wood, D. M. (2009) Adult morphology and terminology. In: Brown, B. V., Borkent, A., Cumming, J. M., Wood, D. M., Woodley, N. E. &amp; Zumbado, M. (Eds.), Manual of Central American Diptera. Vol. 1. NRC Research Press, Ottawa, Ontario, pp. 9 - 50. [Canada]" type="book" year="2009">
Cumming &amp; Wood (
<number box="[388,448,830,854]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" value="2009.0">2009</number>
))
</bibRefCitation>
. Body color brown. Scutellum with brown hairs, with white pleural hairs. Legs redbrown, darkening distally on the tarsi. Tergite 
<number box="[668,682,866,890]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
with a pair of white spots, tergites 
<number box="[1074,1117,866,890]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" value="2.3">2, 3</number>
and 
<number box="[1171,1185,866,890]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
with wide white spots reaching the lateral margins. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Pechuman" box="[630,830,901,926]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" refString="Pechuman, L. L. (1967) A new Pelecorhynchus from Chile (Diptera: Tabanoidea: Pelecorhynchidae). Canadian Entomologist, 99, 554 - 555. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4039 / ent 99554 - 5" type="journal article" year="1967">
Pechuman (
<number box="[761,821,901,926]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, it is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1089,902,925]" class="Insecta" family="Pelecorhynchidae" genus="Pelecorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penai">
<emphasis box="[1003,1089,902,925]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">P. penai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since both species have small white spots on the lateral margin of the tergite 
<number box="[702,716,938,962]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
, a character not observed in other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1251,1429,937,961]" class="Insecta" family="Pelecorhynchidae" genus="Pelecorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1429,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">Pelecorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mackerras" box="[151,452,973,998]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" refString="Mackerras, I. M. &amp; Fuller, M. E. (1942) The genus Pelecorhynchus (Diptera: Tabanoidea). Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 67, 9 - 77" type="journal article" year="1942">
Mackerras &amp; Fuller (
<number box="[386,444,974,998]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" value="1942.0">1942</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that it is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[740,852,973,997]" class="Insecta" family="Pelecorhynchidae" genus="Pelecorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[740,852,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">P. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in that 
<emphasis box="[1065,1183,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">P. k roe b e r i</emphasis>
has white hairs on the pleura, scutellum with distal margin with brown hairs, and legs reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,757,1070]" box="[199,1119,1045,1070]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,495,1045,1070]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from 
<typeStatus box="[709,757,1046,1070]" pageId="10" pageNumber="198">type</typeStatus>
locality, Región de Magallanes.
</paragraph>
